{"id":"5770","name":"I'm getting pulled over - 18 Actions","tagline":"Click of a button or Invoke Siri and exclaim “I’m getting pulled over” to auto-perform 18 actions.","icon":"ios13 c4282601983 g59751","latest":"18426","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"Siri, I'm being pulled over\" src=\"https://img.techpowerup.org/200629/siriimbeingpulledover.png\"></p>\n<p>When launching it for the very first time, You will be prompted to choose your contacts (whom you wish to notify of the incident) twice.\nFirst time is for Action 12 and Second is for Action 15</p>\n<p>Below are the sequential actions performed when running this shortcut:</p>\n<pre><code>Actions 1 - 4:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Make note of your current screen brightness and device volume\nThese values will be used later on at the end, to restore the settings to their original state</p>\n<pre><code>Action 5:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Activates Do Not Disturb until its deactivated</p>\n<pre><code>Actions 6 - 7:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Lowers the Screen brightness and Device volume down to zero percent</p>\n<pre><code>Actions 8 - 12:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note the current Date, Time and your current Geographic location, then formats it neatly and grammatically to be sent as text via iMessage to the chosen contact or contacts including Latitude and Longitude details (in case the address didn’t make sense or doesn’t exist for example in an uncharted location like a large national park or forest</p>\n<pre><code>Actions 13 - 14:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Initiates audio + video recording of the interaction with front facing camera.\nYou will be required to manually STOP the recording when ready, the video will save automatically and Action 15 will resume</p>\n<pre><code>Action 15:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Sends a copy of the video interaction to your chosen contact or contacts</p>\n<pre><code>Actions 16 - 18:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Deactivates Do Not Disturb which was activated by Action 5 and Restores Screen brightness and device volume level to values noted by Actions 1 - 4</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.00 - June 29, 2020, 10:32 p.m.</strong></p>"}